id: pmc-qm7s
title: Support full historical changelog generation from git release tags
description: "Add package-owned full-history generation to pm-changelog so downstream projects can rebuild CHANGELOG.md from actual git release tag windows, with an Unreleased section for post-latest-tag closed work and item links/check mode intact. Mirrors GitHub issue unbraind/pm-changelog#10."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: changelog,ci,git-tags,release
created_at: "2026-05-24T15:23:16.720Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T20:04:52.098Z"
author: codex-changelog-full-history
release: v2026.05.24-13
resolution: completed
expected_result: pm-changelog can generate a full project CHANGELOG.md from actual git release tag windows through package-owned CLI and extension flags.
actual_result: "Published pm-changelog 2026.5.24-12 with --all-release-tags and --release-tag-pattern, full-history release-window tests, docs, CI tag checkout fix, npm latest verification, and GitHub release."
comments[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-24T15:29:52.358Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Evidence: implemented --all-release-tags for CLI and pm extension, including git tag windows with Unreleased, release-window item assignment, docs, and contract tests. npm run release:check passed for pm-changelog@2026.5.24-12."
  "2026-05-24T15:32:20.124Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Linked-test note: default schema sandbox makes changelog:check compare against an empty tracker, so this package release gate must run in tracker context when linked through pm test. Direct npm run release:check passed in the real project context."
  "2026-05-24T15:33:42.987Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Evidence: direct npm run release:check passed, and linked pm test passed with env -u PM_PATH -u PM_GLOBAL_PATH npm run release:check so the package release gate validates against the real package tracker while still being recorded through pm."
  "2026-05-24T15:36:31.291Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"CI follow-up: unbraind/pm-changelog CI failed because actions/checkout was shallow and tag-window changelog checks could not resolve the previous release tag. Updated CI checkout to fetch full history and tags."
  "2026-05-24T15:41:41.220Z",codex-changelog-full-history,"Follow-up: fixed zero-padded calendar tag matching so npm version 2026.5.24-13 can resolve tag v2026.05.24-13 for --until-release-tag and ignore post-tag tracker closure. npm run release:check passed with 25 tests."
